+## Rate limiting
+
+All public API endpoints are rate limited to 100 requests/minute per token.
+Exceeding the limit returns `429 Too Many Requests` with a `Retry-After` header.
+OAuth 2.1 scopes are enforced on every endpoint, and requests without the
+`catalogue:read` scope are rejected with `403 Forbidden`.
